India considered him as one of its most wanted <b>terrorists</b> because of his alleged ties with Lashkar-e-Taiba and his involvement in attacks against India such as the <b>2008 Mumbai terror attacks</b>, therefore Saeed is listed on the<font color ="#386bca">  NIA Most Wanted </font> list and India has banned his organisation as a <font color ="#386bca"> terrorist organisation</font>.The United States,the United Kingdom,the <font color ="#6127a2">European Union</font>, Russia and Australia have also banned LET.Since 2008, various Indian politicians have demanded that Saeed be handed over but there is no extradition treaty between the two countries. Hafiz Saeed states that he has no links with LET and that India has neither evidence nor any real proof behind their allegations.

